    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-06-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="283"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860P.512 Residence/17</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-06-04">June 4,
                            1929</date>.<lb/>[Received June 17.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6191</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Legation’s despatch No. 5840, of
                    January 21, 1929, and to the Department’s Instruction No. 598, of February 12,
                    1929, concerning the removal of the sojourn tax levied on American citizens
                    residing in Latvia, I now have the honor to transmit herewith copies of a Note
                    dated February 27, 1929, from the Legation to the Latvian Foreign Office, and of
                    the latter’s reply, dated June 1, 1929,<note n="9" xml:id="d283fn9">Neither
                        printed.</note> stating that, beginning July 1, 1929, a fee of Lats 10.00
                    per year for the permit of sojourn in Latvia of American citizens shall replace
                    the previous sojourn tax.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. B. <hi rend="smallcaps">Coleman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
